#: ../../wallets/axecore/advanced.rst:320
msgid ""
"It is possible to select between different Axe wallets when starting "
"Axe Core by specifying the ``wallet`` argument, or even run multiple "
"instances of Axe Core simultaneously by specifying separate data "
"directories using the ``datadir`` argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../wallets/axecore/advanced.rst:325
msgid ""
"To begin, install the Axe Core wallet for your system according to the "
":ref:`installation instructions <axecore-installation>`. When you get to"
" the step **Running Axe Core for the first time**, you can decide "
"whether you want to maintain separate ``wallet.dat`` files in the default"
" location (simpler if you do not need to run the wallets simultaneously),"
" or specify entirely separate data directories such as e.g. ``C:\\Axe1``"
" (simpler if you do want to run the wallets simultaneously)."
